<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="worthy-adj">worthy <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'wɜːði/    美 /'wɜːrði/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>值得敬重的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a worthy cause
崇高的事业</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a worthy champion 
当之无愧的冠军</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>值得的：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>(be) worthy of sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>she is a teacher who is worthy of respect
她是位值得尊敬的老师。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He insisted that the problem worthy of attention be discussed at the meeting.
他坚持在会上讨论那个值得关注的问题。</p><footer>2010湖北改</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>(be) worthy to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is worthy to receive such honor.
她应该获得这个荣誉。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The young man is worthy to be taught.
孺子可教。</p></div></div>